info.title: ModelsLab Image Generation API
info.description: A comprehensive API for AI-driven image generation including text-to-image, image-to-image, inpainting, LoRA/Multi LoRA, and model management capabilities.

key.description: Your API Key used for request authorization

request_id.description: Returned by the id parameter in the response upon an image generation request.

key.description: Your API Key used for request authorization.

model_id.description: The ID of the model to be used. It can be a public model or one you have trained.

prompt.description: A text description of what you want in the generated image.

negative_prompt.description: Items you don't want in the image.

init_image.description: Link to the initial image to be used as a reference.

samples.description: The number of images to be returned in the response.

num_inference_steps.description: The number of denoising steps. Values range from 1 to 20, and any value above 20 will be capped at 20.

safety_checker.description: A checker for NSFW images. If detected, such images will be replaced by a blank image. Default is true.

safety_checker_type.description: How to modify the image if NSFW content is found. Default is 'sensitive_content_text'.

enhance_prompt.description: Enhance prompts for better results. Default is true.

enhance_style.description: Allows you to set the style of the image for better results. Refer to documentation for available styles.

tomesd.description: Enable tomesd to generate images quickly. Default is true.

use_karras_sigmas.description: Use Keras sigmas to generate images. Produces nice results. Default is true.

algorithm_type.description: Used in the DPMSolverMultistepScheduler scheduler. Default is 'none'.

vae.description: Use a custom VAE for generating images. Default is null.

lora_strength.description: Specify the strength of the LoRa model(s) you're using. Provide a float value (0.1 to 1) or comma-separated values for multiple LoRAs.

lora_model.description: Pass LoRa model ID(s). Multiple LoRa models are supported; pass comma-separated values (e.g., 'contrast-fix, yae-miko-genshin').

strength.description: Prompt strength when using the initial image. 1.0 corresponds to full destruction of information in the initial image.

seed.description: Used to reproduce results. The same seed will generate the same image again. Pass null for a random number.

scheduler.description: Use this to set a scheduler.

webhook.description: Set a URL to receive a POST API call once image generation is complete.

track_id.description: This ID is returned in the response to the webhook API call and is used to identify the request.

ip_adapter_scale.description: Scale for the IP adapter. Should be between 0 and 1.

ip_adapter_image.description: Valid image URL for the IP adapter.

base64.description: Get the response as a base64 string. Pass init_image as a base64 string to get a base64 response. Default is false.

temp.description: Create a temporary image link valid for 24 hours. Default is false.

key.description: Your API Key used for request authorization.

model_id.description: The ID of the model. Obtain the model ID from the provided source.

prompt.description: A text description of the things you want in the generated image.

negative_prompt.description: Items you don't want in the image.

samples.description: The number of images to be returned in response.

num_inference_steps.description: Number of denoising steps. Values range from 1 to 20, and any value above 20 will be capped at 20.

safety_checker.description: A checker for NSFW images. If detected, such images will be replaced by a blank image. Default is true.

safety_checker_type.description: Modify image if NSFW images are found. Default is 'sensitive_content_text'.

enhance_prompt.description: Enhance prompts for better results. Default is true.

enhance_style.description: Allows you to set the style of the image for better results. Refer to documentation for available styles.

seed.description: Used to reproduce results. The same seed will generate the same image again. Pass null for a random number.

multi_lingual.description: Allow multilingual prompts to generate images. Set to true if using a language other than English in text prompts. Default is false.

panorama.description: Set to true to generate a panorama image. Default is false.

self_attention.description: If you want a high-quality image, set to true. This will take more time. Default is false.

upscale.description: Set to upscale the image resolution. 1: No upscale, 2: 2x upscale, 3: 3x upscale.

lora_model.description: Pass LoRa model ID(s). Multiple LoRa models are supported; pass comma-separated values (e.g., 'contrast-fix,yae-miko-genshin').

lora_strength.description: Specify the strength of the LoRa model(s) you're using. Provide a float value (0.1 to 1) or comma-separated values for multiple LoRAs.

track_id.description: ID returned in the response to the webhook API call, used to identify the request.

base64.description: Get response as a base64 string. Default is false.

highres_fix.description: High-resolution fix for generated image. Default is false.

temp.description: Create a temporary image link valid for 24 hours. Default is false.

instant_response.description: If true, returns future links for queued requests instantly instead of waiting. Default is false.

generationTime.description: Time taken to generate the image in seconds

id.description: Unique identifier for the image generation

nsfw_content_detected.description: Indicates if NSFW content was detected.

meta.description: Metadata about the image generation including all parameters used and more.

tip.description: Additional information or tips for the user

eta.description: Estimated time for completion in seconds (processing status)

fetch_result.description: URL to fetch the result when processing

future_links.description: Array of future image URLs for queued requests
